Function Reference/post comments feed link « WordPress Codex
-----------

Prints out the comment feed link for a post. Link text is placed in the
anchor. If no link text is specified, default text is used. If no post
ID is specified, the current post is used.

Usage
-----

`  <?php   post_comments_feed_link( $link_text = 'link_text', $post_id = 'post_id',         $feed = 'feed_type' );?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$link_text` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Descriptive text.
    Default: 'Comments Feed'

 `$post_id` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Post ID.
    Default: Current post

 `$feed` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Type of feed. Possible values: atom, rdf, rss, rss2.
    Default: rss2

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   Link to the comment feed for the current post.

